properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 3 at 7:27PM MST until January 4 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High winds returning to portions of central Wyoming Saturday...

.An approaching cold front will bring strong winds to portions of
western and central Wyoming late tonight and Saturday.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts 60 to 70 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 8 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Watch for strong cross winds on area roads, including Interstate
25.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. In your home during a windstorm, avoid
activities near windows. Use caution if you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 8 PM MST SATURDAY
